<h2>Are you considering a career in real estate?</h2>
<p>Real Estate as a professional career for the <strong><em>right</em></strong>  person can be both fulfilling and potentially lucrative.  
    You may be  asking yourself &mdash; how do I know if I&rsquo;m the right person &mdash; that I&rsquo;m  suited to the rigours of real estate sales? 
    The simple answer is there&rsquo;s  only one way to know for sure and that&rsquo;s to complete the pre-licensing  course offered by the governing body
     of your State or Province and give  it a try. <a href="http://www.homelife.ca/careers.homelife#linkscountry"><strong>Links</strong></a> have been 
    provided to the various governing bodies further down on this page.</p>
<h2>Do you have what it takes?</h2>
    <p>A career in Real Estate can be exciting and fulfilling, but it can  also represent a big step in a person's life. Real Estate sales is a  commission only business, meaning that you only generate income when you  successfully help someone buy or sell a home.  Being skilled at  budgeting is therefore essential skill.</p>
                <p>In order to assist customers with their buying and selling needs, you  must first find them. This is known as prospecting for business and is  an essential part of every successful Realtors day.</p>
    <h2>Results Oriented Training</h2>
    <p>At HomeLife&trade;, we take your training and development needs seriously.  Whether you are a new Realtor looking to start your business, or an  existing Realtor looking to take your business to the next level; our  HomeLife University has the sales training you&rsquo;ll need to take control  of your future and build your real estate career!</p>
                <p id="step4"><strong>If you are a goal-driven, service oriented  entrepreneur who is serious about building a successful real estate  career and making a difference, then joining HomeLife&trade; is the right  choice for you.</strong></p>
                <p>A HomeLife&trade; sales representative embodies many of the characteristics and strategies listed below:</p>
   <div class="Free-Home_new">
     <ol>
                    <li><strong>Have Focused Goals</strong> &mdash; HomeLife&trade; sales  representatives are success oriented and focused on short and long term  business goals. These defined goals and planned activities are evaluated  and adjusted regularly to meet changes such as market shifts.  Underpinning sales representative efforts is a commitment and passion  for success.</li>
                    <li><strong>Willing to go Beyond Sales to Build a Practice</strong> &mdash;  Sales representatives who have successful real estate careers systemize  processes in order to better manage time and be organized. Able to  prioritize tasks and productive activities, <strong>successful sales representatives</strong>  nurture and build trust and confidence with a database of contacts that  understand the Higher Standards&trade; of HomeLife&trade; real estate service.</li>
                    <li><strong>Specialize in Specific Target Markets</strong> &mdash; Instead of choosing too broad an approach, <strong>successful sales representatives</strong>  identify three to four areas that fit their skills, experience and  personality. Whether it's a geographical focus or concentration on  commercial or luxury properties, highly skilled sales representatives  choose to work with whom they like and who have similar interests.</li>
                    <li><strong>Are Great at Time Management</strong> &mdash; Successful sales  representatives have a vision and a plan that operates as a starting  point for implementation. To maintain clarity and focus, and to get the  best payoff for time invested, sales representatives choose high  leverage activities such as maintaining contact with database clients.  With a dollar-productivity mindset, focused sales representatives are  committed to a daily productivity plan, are self-propelled and realize  that discipline is the key to maximizing time.</li>
                    <li><strong>Are Early Adopters of Technology</strong> &mdash; Sales  representatives consistently deliver Higher Standards&trade; service that  exceeds client expectations. It is important to learn new technology  that will help facilitate and systemize the real estate process.</li>
                    <li><strong>Know The Primary Objective Is Marketing</strong> &mdash; Sales  representatives know that business development and marketing are just as  important as sales. Such professionals understand the value of a  compelling marketing plan that defines their unique selling proposition  and incorporates the HomeLife&trade; portfolio of innovative and affordable  marketing systems.</li>
                    <li><strong>Connect and Consistently Follow Up with Prospects</strong> &mdash;  While effective marketing is good for attracting leads, following up is  the key to convert such leads into successful transactions. Successful  sales representatives know the value of a database that helps them  maintain contact with future prospects to build trust, rapport and  confidence in their service. <strong>Successful sales representatives</strong>  are patient, dedicated and do not give up on leads. People prefer  professionals whom they trust and know will keep on top of things.</li>
                    <li><strong>Have A High Level of Integrity, A Healthy Ego and An Optimistic Attitude.</strong>  &mdash; Vital to the growth of a successful sales representative's business  is the core belief that he or she will win and that anything can be  achieved with focus and effort. Integral to outstanding achievement is a  healthy ego to help sales representatives maintain faith and confidence  in their ideas in order to reach peak performance.</li>
                    <li><strong>Build Networks of Influential People</strong> &mdash; Sales  representatives proactively network with influential people as well as  build and maintain relationships within a community. They form a large  sphere of influence, which generates high-level referrals and powerful  testimonials.</li>
                    <li><strong>Work Hard: Under-Promise and Over-Deliver</strong> &mdash; Sales  representatives who thrive have high values and operate ethically. They  do not take short cuts but, rather, strive to achieve the highest  standards in all they do. Patience, integrity, hard work and a  determination not to settle for anything less than the best underpin a  dedication to Higher Standards&trade; in all their real estate activities.</li>
                    <li><strong>Are Great Communicators and Active Listeners</strong> &mdash;  Patient communicators ask pertinent questions and acknowledge answers,  sales representatives who excel are always determined to define a  client's needs and desires. Active listeners, they base client  communication on facts and market statistics.</li>
                    <li><strong>Consistently Invest in Self-Development</strong> &mdash; Focused  on constant improvement, such sales representatives always read  industry-related information, attend seminars, listen to audio programs,  participate in continuing education programs and exchange ideas with  colleagues.</li>
                    <li><strong>Know the Local Real Estate Rules and Regulations</strong> &mdash;  Success is the result of taking the time and effort to become true  professionals. Current knowledge of all local, state/provincial, and  national guidelines allows them to work in their client&rsquo;s best interest.</li>
                </ol>
